One that can definitely be your bestest friend & love his fur brothers too, BUT that when sh*t happens that dog turns the f*ck on until you turn him off. Yes, you’d have to learn how to accept guests differently, but it’s just a matter of you being trained how to properly introduce people & your dog being trained to know that YOU are in control, YOU are to be trusted w/who you let in. Many times just the ferocious bark of a German Shepherd or Rottweiler is enough to get the person to leave, keep people away from your house. Do some breed research on the best family/multi pet household protection breeds. Rottweilers are near the top. Rotts will also protect the other animals in the home as they see them as part of their family. That’s kinda what you’d be looking for since you’ll likely always be a multi pet home. Yes, this training is expensive, yes, a pure bred, vetted/healthy guard dog is expensive, but for your situation it’s well worth it. I’m very relieved nothing bad happened to you guys.
